South African doctor: Omicron is highly transmissible but mostly mild.
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe that the Omicron variant of COVID-19 causes more mild symptoms than the Delta variant, although it spreads faster.
According to the Associated Press, as the Omicron variant spreads in South Africa, a group of more than 5,000 doctors in Gauteng Province, South Africa, reported that the new crown patients they are currently treating have mild symptoms, such as body pain and cough, which are similar to the flu.
Dr. Unben Pillay, the director of the organization, said he sees dozens of patients every day, but no patients need to be hospitalized.
"They were able to control the disease at home, and most people recovered within 10 to 14 days of isolation," Pillay said.
This includes older patients and those with health problems, who are more likely to fall seriously ill from COVID-19 infection, he said.
In contrast, he said, in the last wave of the Delta outbreak, the new-crowned patients he treated "had difficulty breathing and low blood oxygen levels."
Many people will be hospitalized in a few days.
In the two weeks after the first report of the Omicron mutant strain in southern Africa, other doctors shared similar experiences.
Although it will take several weeks to collect enough data, doctors' observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the South African National Institute of Infectious Diseases, only 30% of the COVID-19 patients hospitalized in recent weeks were seriously ill, half the rate of severe illness in the previous wave, and the average length of hospitalization was reduced from 8 days to 2.8 days. Only 3% of COVID-19 patients died recently, compared to 20% in the early outbreak in South Africa.
Willem Hanekom, director of the African Health Institute, citing data from the National Institute of Infectious Diseases and other reports, said: "At present, almost all indications are that this is a mild disease."
He added: "It's still early, and we need to get the data later."
Normally, hospitalizations and deaths occur later, and we have only been in this wave for two weeks."
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are watching the number of cases and hospitalization rates, while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
Although Delta remains the world's leading COVID-19 strain, Omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, with South Africa as the epicenter of the epidemic.
According to health officials, the number of new cases detected in Gauteng increased by 400% in the first week of December, with tests showing that the Omicron variant accounts for more than 90% of cases.
Education Commentary: What is it to save abducted children?
If we are analogous to the famous public service advertisement saying "no sale, no killing," then in a good environment where there is no demand for "abduction," mass prevention and control, and anti-abduction by the whole people, make abduction and trafficking unprofitable, risky, and costly, and such crimes will not occur repeatedly.
Recently, the emergency information release platform for missing children developed by the Anti-Abduction Office of the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security was launched.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for the release of information on missing children and to retrieve abducted children in a timely manner.
Hearing that this app is called "Reunion", I felt very warm.
The new technology means not only the name "literature and art" and full of feelings, but also the proper use of information, practical and effective.
The primary goal of anti-abduction law enforcement is to retrieve abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of the suspect.
The significance of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education, can list many "big words."
However, before the abduction and trafficking cases are solved, priority should be given to the personal safety of the victims.
In the context of the urgent "rescue" purpose, such as "whether all abductions and trafficking in children should be punished by death" and other controversial topics can be put aside for a while and discussed with caution, but the rescue of abducted children is not allowed.
Based on the experience of investigating such cases, traffickers are accustomed to stay away from the crime site as soon as possible after they are successful.
If the abduction operation is delayed for one more minute, the child may be one step further away from the parents, and the difficulty of detecting the case will increase by one point.
In this case, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with an effective method such as the "Reunion" platform that directly helps to solve the case and recover the child.
After all, "fighting trafficking" is a big task that needs to be done by operating the entire legal system.
To fight crime and protect the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation to the protection of the judiciary and the meticulous law enforcement, there is no need to implement the care of "protecting children and helping the weak."
In addition, the prevention of child abduction and trafficking, from the family to the society, can be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three was resting at the train station, and the parents were asleep and woke up to find that the child was missing.
A two-year-old child cannot be expected to have sufficient self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, he should at least have a considerable sense of protection.
Taking turns to rest between parents, or placing the child under secure protection, is the minimum means to prevent child abduction.
From the other side of the police crackdown on the crime of abduction and trafficking, the party who buys abducted children should also be concerned and punished.
A single illegal act is often just a link in a long chain.
According to the Criminal Law of China, the statutory starting point for the crime of abduction and trafficking of children is five years; if the circumstances are particularly serious, the penalty may be death and confiscation of property.
The starting point is high and the maximum penalty is severe. Under the general trend of "lighter punishment," the crime of child abduction and trafficking is obviously a crime with heavier punishment.
But there are still many cases of abduction and trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people have backward concepts in raising children and weak legal awareness.
Legal education for these people should be followed up simultaneously.
To effectively control the crime of abduction and trafficking, it is not possible to rely only on strict law enforcement by the authorities.
If the "market" for abduction and trafficking is widespread, the abductors are interested in profit, and constantly innovate the means of abduction and trafficking, so as to form a situation of "fighting law" with law enforcement, anti-abduction operations will inevitably fall into the mire of inefficiency.
Therefore, the elimination of backward concepts and the popularization of common legal knowledge will also help to eradicate the crimes of abduction, trafficking and buying children.
