The image sparked controversy after surfing the Internet.
Some netizens believed that this was an "eyeball begging behavior," and many netizens expressed sympathy for it.
"We discovered the situation when we patrolled the square at about 10 a.m. on the 23rd, and there were already a lot of onlookers."
