Educational Thinking: How to Make "Learning Bully" and "Learning Slag" in College Examinations - Xinhuanet
Three students from Lanzhou Jiaotong University wrote to the university leadership, reflecting their confusion about the university exam, and proposing to improve the difficulty of the exam and change the test question types so that the exam truly reflects the students' actual level.
Indeed, for a long time, college exams have been a hot topic.
On university campuses, students come from all over the world, with different levels of ability, and with different levels of learning, the learning situation varies widely.
It is inevitable that there will be different feelings about the assessment of groups with such diverse characteristics.
Of course, if the test questions are of a single type, the repetition rate is high, and the questions are too simple, it will inevitably lead to a completely different feeling.
Students who do not work hard may be able to pass the exam by concentrating on the attack before the exam. If they think of other methods, they may achieve a multiplier effect with half the effort.
As a result, there is a "strange situation" in which "learning scum" can pass the test without investment and even get high marks, and "learning bully" never drops out of class, has good homework and notes, and the exams are not much higher.
From this point of view, it is not unreasonable for students of Lanzhou Jiaotong University to report problems in university exams, and I believe that this situation is not unique to Lanzhou Jiaotong University.
In this sense, I would like to praise the three students who wrote the letter.
In fact, people who have gone to college know that it is not uncommon to prepare for exams by surprise, try to "get" test questions from teachers in various ways, and strive to delineate the scope of the exam, and get "key tutoring" before the exam. It is not even uncommon to have a small copy in the exam and ask the teacher to raise your hand after the exam.
In my opinion, as a kind of teaching quality assessment guidance, the measure of a university's passing or not is more about the teachers' comprehensive grasp of teaching and learning, and the scientific propositions based on it.
Entering the undergraduate stage, majors begin to be subdivided, and many professional courses focus on basic knowledge.
There is no doubt that whether to fully grasp the basic knowledge of a subject is the content to be examined in the university examination.
Undergraduate knowledge is basically the basic theory of the subject and basic common sense. From the point of knowledge, the space for change is not large, and it is basically fixed.
As a teacher said, "The basic knowledge of college mathematics 20 years ago is still being learned, and it is still the key."
However, the knowledge point is basically unchanged, which does not mean that the test questions are single and the test questions are repeated.
In many universities, the examination is usually composed of question groups, and the examination papers are composed by the senior teachers of the subject, and the examination papers are also taken by all the teachers who are responsible for the subject, so that the repetition of the test questions can be overcome to a certain extent.
However, it is necessary to draw up a set of test questions that conform to the actual teaching and learning situation, and the questions are easily distributed in a normal way according to the overall situation of students' learning. It is also necessary to comprehensively grasp the teaching situation and comprehensively analyze the degree of students' learning, so that the test propositions have a dynamic grasp of the difficulty and the type of questions, which can not only highlight the basic knowledge, but also take into account the ability test, and at the same time, innovate the design of the question types.
Examinations are the baton of university education. What kind of exams there are, students will have corresponding preparation plans for the exams, which will affect the effectiveness of university education in the long run.
The Lanzhou Jiaotong University administration attaches great importance to the students' letter of recommendation, and has deployed a rectification plan throughout the university.
All teaching units are required to organize teachers to conduct seminars and self-examination of the final exam of the course, formulate test paper propositions and related systems, and strengthen the supervision and inspection of the test paper propositions and examination links, refine the evaluation of grades, and strengthen the comprehensive evaluation of all aspects of the course teaching.
To solve the problem of single type of test questions and repetitive questions from the mechanism is a problem that university exams need to face, and of course a corresponding system needs to be put in place, but kung fu is expensive in daily life, and teachers need to have a comprehensive grasp of the teaching situation, not only to understand the teaching content, but also to understand the students' learning situation, and to understand both sides of the test, teaching and learning will be better connected, forming a positive interaction, and the examination will be more in line with the actual situation, so that "learning bully" and "scum" will each have their own place.
