Don't scare people at the starting line - Xinhuanet
When you visit the book market, you can often feel the popularity of successful books.
Many of today's success books preach the "best principle" - that is, assuming or implying that you can "do" it, and then telling you what you need to do.
It is equivalent to saying that the most important and fundamental link of "how to do it" has been crossed at once.
Because of this, these books all have a common feature - either do your best at once, or do nothing at all; either 100, or 0; either you climb Mount Tai, or you just stay where you are.
This "best principle" will be recognized as "correct" by anyone who looks at it, but 99% of people will be intimidated at the starting line.
Because this theory advocates a path of "you have to make up your mind, reinvent yourself, and make a 180-degree transformation," which is precisely the fatal weakness of many people.
For a person who sticks to the rules, conforms to the old ways, and refuses to change, you must shout "You want to change" in his ear, which is undoubtedly self-deception and playing the piano to the swine.
The vast majority of people will be timid in the face of the word "change" and will not move forward, making it difficult to make a decision; or they will make a determination to "change" with a sudden impulse and take the first step bravely, but often it is not a long time, and they will not persist for a long time before they lose, and it is difficult to see continuity.
Mr. Ma Sanli's famous crosstalk of "Starting Tomorrow" is the most vivid expression of this "universal human nature" classic.
The biggest problem with the "best principle" is that the threshold is too high, and it often exceeds the limit of ordinary people's ability, making the vast majority of people "look at the door and sigh."
Perhaps the "second best principle" is the way that it is possible to put more ordinary people on the road to relative success.
The core of the "second best principle" is to "lower the threshold" - it encourages the theory that if you can't do 100, you can only do 1: Because 1 is always greater than 0; if you can't climb Mount Tai, you can only climb the small sand dunes in front of your house, because that is better than standing still.
In short, as long as you do something, it is better than not doing it.
Since the threshold has been greatly lowered, there is more possibility for ordinary people to persevere, and as long as they persevere in everything, the probability of success will increase.
It's just that the road to success that follows the "second best principle" is a little longer.
All in all, although the "best principle" is ostensibly a success for all, it ultimately inspires a few, while the "second best principle" can effectively inspire more people and benefit as many people as possible.
The resource reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake increased by 0.71 million tons this year - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, December 11 (Reporters: Luo Xiaofei, Zhang Hongxiang) The reporter learned from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs that the latest monitoring results show that the reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake increased by 7,100 tons this year compared to the previous year, to 108,500 tons, a cumulative increase of more than 40 times compared to the initial protection period in 2002.
The Qinghai Lake naked carp, commonly known as "Huangyu," is a unique and precious fish species in Qinghai Lake, which plays a pivotal role in maintaining the safety and biodiversity of the "water-fish-bird" ecological chain in the Qinghai Lake Basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake decreased sharply due to the large number of human hunts and the increasingly degraded environment in the breeding waters of naked carp, and in 2002, the reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake were only 2,592 tons.
In 2004, the Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the Red List of Chinese Species.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has closed the lake to fish breeding, prohibiting any unit, collective or individual from fishing for naked carp in Qinghai Lake and major rivers and tributaries in the lake area, and prohibiting the sale of naked carp and its products.
At the same time, the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake have been increasing year by year through measures such as artificial breeding and discharge, cleaning up the main river channels of Qinghai Lake and designing scientific and reasonable "fish passageways."
Yang Lin, deputy director of the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, said that up to now, the Qinghai Lake naked carp has been artificially propagated and released nearly 180 million tails, contributing more than 23% to the recovery of Qinghai Lake naked carp resources.
The source area of the three rivers in Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in China and even in Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological function area to control the eastward spread of desertification in the west.
In order to protect the ecological environment in the source areas of the Three Rivers and Qinghai Lake, protect aquatic wildlife, and maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has issued a notice on the prohibition of fishing in key waters of the Yangtze River, Yellow River, and Qinghai Lake since the beginning of this year, and has established a comprehensive management system for the prohibition of fishing in "one river, one lake."
