"Last year, the Geminid meteor shower was very impressive, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, and the intensity will be reduced."
The 14th is the 11th of the 11th lunar month, and the moon phase is a convex moon. The bright moonlight will interfere with the observation. Fortunately, the moon will set in the middle of the night, and the radiant point of the Geminid meteor shower will also rise higher.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe in the late hours of the night after the moon, but pay attention to cold and warm.
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not recommended to observe in cities. You can choose a place in the suburbs or villages with high altitude, low light pollution, and a wide field of view facing the northeast, and then wait patiently until the moon sets and you can observe it visually."
It should be noted that the Geminid meteor shower has a large flow in all directions, so you don't have to stare at the radiant point of the Geminid meteor shower all the time.
If you want to shoot a gorgeous meteor shower, you should choose a wide-angle, large-aperture lens, and use a high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
